CLIV. 1. COMPLAINT OF LADY ANNE GORDON⁷S PET PARROT.

This is the first of a triad of similar jenx d'esprit, dealing with domestic pets. These seem to have been in Johnston's days as necessary a part of a happy household as they are found to be at the present day. There is much humour in the mode in which their rival claims are presented and domestic peace is supposed to be maintained.
